Pyperclip is a cross-platform Python module for copy and paste clipboard functions.
The pyperclip module has copy() and paste() functions that can send text to and receive text from your computerâ€™s clipboard. 
Sending the output of your program to the clipboard will make it easy to paste it on an email, word processor, or some other software.

Installing pyperclip:

pip install pyperclip

To copy text to the clipboard, pass a string to pyperclip.copy(). 
To paste the text from the clipboard, call pyperclip.paste() and the text will be returned as a string value.
